{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.29",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 29 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:1",
      "text": "Moreover Job continued his parable, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:2",
      "text": "Oh that I were as in months past, as in the days when God preserved me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:3",
      "text": "When his candle shined upon my head, and when by his light I walked through darkness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:4",
      "text": "As I was in the days of my youth, when the secret of God was upon my tabernacle;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:5",
      "text": "When the Almighty was yet with me, when my children were about me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:6",
      "text": "When I washed my steps with butter, and the rock poured me out rivers of oil;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:7",
      "text": "When I went out to the gate through the city, when I prepared my seat in the street!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:8",
      "text": "The young men saw me, and hid themselves: and the aged arose, and stood up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:9",
      "text": "The princes refrained talking, and laid their hand on their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:10",
      "text": "The nobles held their peace, and their tongue cleaved to the roof of their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:11",
      "text": "When the ear heard me, then it blessed me; and when the eye saw me, it gave witness to me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:12",
      "text": "Because I delivered the poor that cried, and the fatherless, and him that had none to help him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:13",
      "text": "The blessing of him that was ready to perish came upon me: and I caused the widow’s heart to sing for joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:14",
      "text": "I put on righteousness, and it clothed me: my judgment was as a robe and a diadem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:15",
      "text": "I was eyes to the blind, and feet was I to the lame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:16",
      "text": "I was a father to the poor: and the cause which I knew not I searched out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:17",
      "text": "And I brake the jaws of the wicked, and plucked the spoil out of his teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:18",
      "text": "Then I said, I shall die in my nest, and I shall multiply my days as the sand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:19",
      "text": "My root was spread out by the waters, and the dew lay all night upon my branch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:20",
      "text": "My glory was fresh in me, and my bow was renewed in my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:21",
      "text": "Unto me men gave ear, and waited, and kept silence at my counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:22",
      "text": "After my words they spake not again; and my speech dropped upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:23",
      "text": "And they waited for me as for the rain; and they opened their mouth wide as for the latter rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:24",
      "text": "If I laughed on them, they believed it not; and the light of my countenance they cast not down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.29.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:25",
      "text": "I chose out their way, and sat chief, and dwelt as a king in the army, as one that comforteth the mourners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
